events.name: Wake Forest Demon Deacons at Clemson Tigers

headlines.shortLinkText: Boyd eclipses 100 TDs as Clemson cruises

events.name: Wisconsin Badgers at Ohio State Buckeyes

headlines.description: Braxton Miller threw a career-high four touchdown passes in his first game in three weeks and No. 4 Ohio State ran the nation's longest winning streak to 17 games with a 31-24 victory over No. 23 Wisconsin on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ohio St. gets Miller back, wins

events.name: Stanford Cardinal at Washington State Cougars

headlines.description: Kevin Hogan picked apart Washington State, throwing for 286 yards and three touchdowns, and No. 5 Stanford won its 12th straight with a 55-17 rout of the Cougars on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stanford drubs Wazzu

events.name: LSU Tigers at Georgia Bulldogs

headlines.description: Aaron Murray threw four touchdown passes, including a 25-yarder to Justin Scott-Wesley with 1:47 remaining, and No. 9 Georgia rallied to beat No. 6 LSU 44-41 in a thrilling game between Southeastern Conference powerhouses.
headlines.shortLinkText: Georgia outlasts LSU in slugfest

events.name: Florida State Seminoles at Boston College Eagles

headlines.description: Jameis Winston threw for four touchdowns, including a 55-yard Hail Mary as time expired in the first half to help No. 8 Florida State rally from a slow start and beat Boston College 48-34 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: FSU hits Hail Mary in win

events.name: Texas A&M Aggies at Arkansas Razorbacks

headlines.description: Johnny Manziel accounted for 320 total yards of offense and threw two touchdown passes to Mike Evans as No. 10 Texas A&M pulled away for a 45-33 win over Arkansas on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Manziel, Texas A&M get by Arkansas

events.name: Oklahoma State Cowboys at West Virginia Mountaineers

headlines.description: Clint Trickett threw a touchdown pass in his first start at West Virginia, Ishmael Banks returned an interception for a touchdown and the Mountaineers shocked No. 11 Oklahoma State 30-21 on Saturday.

events.name: South Carolina Gamecocks at UCF Knights

headlines.description: Mike Davis rushed 26 times for 167 yards and three touchdowns, as No. 12 South Carolina overcame an injury to its starting quarterback, four turnovers and a 10-0 halftime deficit to beat UCF 28-25 on Saturday.
